<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97706569415162></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97706569415162><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=625&mid=97706569415162>Full Quest Details</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 17th 3:08 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, here goes the full details on this quest... Yes, I know what I'm talking about, just completed it 24 times for faction working towards my Hero Bracer =P<br><br>Ok, first, you need to be at least high indifferent in Halas, which is not hard, as you can turn in gnoll fangs to Lysbith McNaff in the Pit of Doom 3 at a time for fast faction raises...<br><br>Go to Dargon McPherson, and tell him "I will deliver an elixir to young warriors"... He will then give you the elixir and tell you to take it to EverFrost Peaks and find Talin O'Donal and give it to him, he will then tell you who and where the next person is (there's 4 total, and you must deliver it in order of the NPCs or it will not work)...<br><br>Talin O'Donal can be found by the 2 tents just as you come out of Halas... /loc is 3619 by 666...  He'll then tell you to take it to Bryndin McMill (note the name correction here from the original post) who was last seen near 2 guards... Yes, the is the "2 guard post" by Snowflake... /loc is 2030 by neg1134...  He'll then tell you to take it to Arnis McLish, who was last seen heading towards BlackBurrow... His /loc is normally neg1596 by neg169 (just outside of BlackBurrow ramp) but he does wander off a little bit... If he's not there, give him a few minutes, he'll be back...  He'll then tell you to take it to Megan O'Reilly, and he'll mention Snowflake if you talk to him...  You don't really need Snowflake's help to find Megan if you don't want, she's located near the North Tower at /loc 2046 by neg3982... She also wanders off, so if she's not by the tower, give her a few minutes, she'll also be back...  If you don't want to try and find her by yourself, go back to 2 Guard, Hail Snowflake, and say "Where is Megan"... He'll bark at you, and lead you right to here...   Once you have given the bottle to Megan, she'll tell you to take it back to Dargon, and maybe he'll refill it for you... He won't but in return, you'll get a few copper pieces, and usually a random item... I've gotten everything from a ration to Large Patchwork Leggings (this stuff is nice to give to newbies as you're running by =P)<br><br>This quest take LESS than 13minutes to complete with SoW once you know the route...  (Not sure who the hell came up with an hour.../shrug)<br><br>You will get the following faction increases:<br><br>Wolves of the North<br>Shamen of Justice<br>Merchants of Halas<br>Steel Warriors<br><br>I am well kindly in all of Halas now... although I'm dubious still to the banker, think he's on the rogue faction... OH, there are NO NEGATIVE faction hits either... Ain't it great?!?!  =P<br><br>Hope this helps a little bit...  Good luck all<br><br>Britack, Human Ranger of the 43rd Season, Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
